    "<div style='background:#4a4a4a;color:white;padding:36px 48px;text-align:center;border-radius:10px;'>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h1 style='color:white;font-weight:bold;margin:0;'>Traffic Sign Recognition</h1>\n",
    "<h2 style='color:white;font-weight:bold;margin-top:8px;'>Deep Learning Approach &mdash; GTSRB Dataset</h2>\n",
    "\n",
    "<hr style='border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);margin:16px 0;'>\n",
    "\n",
    "<h3 style='color:white;font-weight:bold;'>Abdulrahman Ageeli &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Ali Alqarni</h3>\n",
    "<h4 style='color:white;font-weight:bold;'>Deep Learning Course &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Supervised by Dr. Majdi Khalid</h4>\n",
    "\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<div style='background:#4a4a4a;color:white;padding:14px 22px;border-radius:6px;font-size:20px;font-weight:bold;'>\n",
    "1 &middot; Introduction & Dataset\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style='padding:16px 6px;font-size:16px;line-height:1.8;color:#000;font-weight:bold;'>\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Dataset:** German Traffic Sign Recognition Benchmark (GTSRB).\n",
    "- **Task:** Multi-class classification (43 distinct classes of road signs).\n",
    "- **Properties:** Images vary wildly in lighting, blur, occlusion, and physical resolution.\n",
    "- **Class Imbalance:** Highly skewed distribution (some classes have 200 samples, others over 2,000).\n",
    "  - *Mitigation:* Handled via **Stratified Splitting** and **Class-Weighted Cross Entropy Loss** to prevent majority-class bias.\n",
    "\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<table style='width:100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top:10px; font-weight:bold; color:#000;'>\n",
    "  <tr style='background:#f2f2f2; border-bottom:2px solid #ccc;'>\n",
    "    <th style='padding:10px; text-align:left;'>Subset</th>\n",
    "    <th style='padding:10px; text-align:left;'>Samples</th>\n",
    "    <th style='padding:10px; text-align:left;'>Purpose</th>\n",
    "  </tr>\n",
    "  <tr style='border-bottom:1px solid #eee;'>\n",
    "    <td style='padding:10px;'>Train Set</td>\n",
    "    <td style='padding:10px;'>31,367</td>\n",
    "    <td style='padding:10px;'>Gradient updates</td>\n",
    "  </tr>\n",
    "  <tr style='border-bottom:1px solid #eee;'>\n",
    "    <td style='padding:10px;'>Validation Set</td>\n",
    "    <td style='padding:10px;'>7,842</td>\n",
    "    <td style='padding:10px;'>Hyperparameter tuning & Early Stopping</td>\n",
    "  </tr>\n",
    "  <tr style='border-bottom:2px solid #ccc;'>\n",
    "    <td style='padding:10px;'>Test Set</td>\n",
    "    <td style='padding:10px;'>12,630</td>\n",
    "    <td style='padding:10px;'>Final independent generalization evaluation</td>\n",
    "  </tr>\n",
    "</table>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<div style='background:#4a4a4a;color:white;padding:14px 22px;border-radius:6px;font-size:20px;font-weight:bold;'>\n",
    "2 &middot; Training Infrastructure & Regularization\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style='padding:16px 6px;font-size:16px;line-height:1.8;color:#000;font-weight:bold;'>\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Augmentation Pipeline:** Random Rotation ($\pm 15^\circ$), Sharpness/Color jittering, and Random Perspective transformations to enrich invariance constraints.\n",
    "- **Optimization:** AdamW optimizer with a **Cosine Annealing Learning Rate Schedule** for smooth convergence towards narrow minima.\n",
    "- **Advanced Regularization:** \n",
    "  - **Label Smoothing (0.1):** Prevents the model from becoming overly confident, smoothing the logit space.\n",
    "  - **Mixed-Precision (FP16):** Accelerated compute using NVIDIA Tensor Cores.\n",
    "  - **Gradient Clipping (max_norm=1.0):** Stabilizes backpropagation updates.\n",
    "\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<div style='background:#4a4a4a;color:white;padding:14px 22px;border-radius:6px;font-size:20px;font-weight:bold;'>\n",
    "3 &middot; Model 1: Custom Deep CNN\n",
    "</div>\n",
    "\n",
    "<div style='padding:16px 6px;font-size:16px;line-height:1.8;color:#000;font-weight:bold;'>\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Design Principle:** 3 stacked structural blocks utilizing dual $3\\times3$ convolutions before spatial downsampling to widen the receptive field smoothly.\n",
    "- **Structural Optimizations:**\n",
    "  - <span style='color:#c0392b;'>**`bias=False` Efficiency:**</span> Omitted bias parameters preceding all BatchNorm steps to eradicate numerical redundancy.\n",
    "  - <span style='color:#c0392b;'>**`Dropout2d` Regularization:**</span> Promoted to 2D Spatial Dropout inside feature blocks to discard entire feature maps, preventing co-adaptation.\n",
    "  - **Global Average Pooling (GAP):** Collapses spatial matrices down to $1\\times1$, massively curtailing dense parameter bottlenecks.\n",
    "  - **Kaiming (He) Normal Initialization:** Custom isolated sub-routine strictly enforcing variance stability across ReLU active networks.\n",
    "\n",
    "</div>"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import torch\n",
    "import torch.nn as nn\n",
    "\n",
    "class TrafficSignCNN(nn.Module):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, num_classes=43):\n",
    "        super().__init__()\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Engineering Practice: bias=False avoids redundancy when combined with BatchNorm\n",
    "        def block(ic, oc):\n",
    "            return nn.Sequential(\n",
    "                nn.Conv2d(ic, oc, kernel_size=3, padding=1, bias=False),\n",
    "                nn.BatchNorm2d(oc),\n",
    "                nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n",
    "                nn.Conv2d(oc, oc, kernel_size=3, padding=1, bias=False),\n",
    "                nn.BatchNorm2d(oc),\n",
    "                nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n",
    "                nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2),\n",
    "                nn.Dropout2d(p=0.25) # Optimized spatial regularization\n",
    "            )\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Consolidated Feature Extraction Pipeline\n",
    "        self.features = nn.Sequential(\n",
    "            block(3, 32),   # Block 1: Basic structural edges & color transitions\n",
    "            block(32, 64),  # Block 2: Complex spatial geometric shapes & corners\n",
    "            block(64, 128)  # Block 3: High-level semantic sign signatures\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "        # GAP maps structural channels smoothly to single nodes\n",
    "        self.gap = nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((1, 1))\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Non-Linear Dense Classification Head\n",
    "        self.classifier = nn.Sequential(\n",
    "            nn.Flatten(),\n",
    "            nn.Linear(128, 256, bias=False),\n",
    "            nn.BatchNorm1d(256),\n",
    "            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),\n",
    "            nn.Dropout(p=0.5),\n",
    "            nn.Linear(256, num_classes) # Raw Logits outputs\n",
    "        )\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Custom Explicit Structural Initialization Run\n",
    "        self._init_weights()\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _init_weights(self):\n",
    "        for m in self.modules():\n",
    "            if isinstance(m, nn.Conv2d):\n",
    "                nn.init.kaiming_normal_(m.weight, nonlinearity='relu')\n",
    "            elif isinstance(m, (nn.BatchNorm2d, nn.BatchNorm1d)):\n",
    "                nn.init.ones_(m.weight)\n",
    "                nn.init.zeros_(m.bias)\n",
    "            elif isinstance(m, nn.Linear):\n",
    "                nn.init.kaiming_normal_(m.weight, nonlinearity='relu')\n",
    "                if m.bias is not None:\n",
    "                    nn.init.zeros_(m.bias)\n",
    "\n",
    "    def forward(self, x):\n",
    "        return self.classifier(self.gap(self.features(x)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Model Instantiation & Pipeline Validation\n",
    "cnn_model = TrafficSignCNN(num_classes=43).to('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')\n",
    "total_params = sum(p.numel() for p in cnn_model.parameters())\n",
    "print(f\"Custom CNN Total Trainable Parameters: {total_params:,}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Input structural validation test\n",
    "with torch.no_grad():\n",
    "    dummy_input = torch.zeros(2, 3, 32, 32).to('cuda' if torch.cuda.is_available() else 'cpu')\n",
    "    print(f\"Structural Sanity Check Pass! Shape Out: {tuple(cnn_model(dummy_input).shape)}\")"
   ]
  },
